    <div class="story-card__description">
                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/the-repatriation-project">The Repatriation Project</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/what-its-like-to-report-on-repatriation">
                                    We Carry the Burden of Repatriating Our Ancestors. Here’s What It’s Like to Report on the Process as an Indigenous Journalist.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Mary Hudetz describes the financial cost and emotional distress that tribal communities face as they continue to wait for the return of the remains of their ancestors, thousands of which are held in museums across the country.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mary-hudetz">Mary Hudetz</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-08-09EDT06:00">Aug. 9, 2023, 6 a.m. EDT</time>
